File: gdocs.info,  Node: Error handling and retries,  Next: Progress indication,  Up: API client

6.1 Error handling and retries
==============================

All API requests include automatic retry logic for transient errors.
When the server returns HTTP 429 (rate limited), 500 (internal server
error), or 503 (service unavailable), the request is retried with
exponential backoff up to three times.  If the response includes a
‘Retry-After’ header, its value is used as the delay; otherwise, the
delay follows the pattern 1s, 2s, 4s, capped at 30 seconds.

   Authentication failures (HTTP 401 or 403) produce a clear error
message directing you to run ‘gdocs-authenticate’ to re-authorize.


File: gdocs.info,  Node: Progress indication,  Prev: Error handling and retries,  Up: API client

6.2 Progress indication
=======================

While API requests are in flight, the global modeline displays ‘[GDocs:
syncing...]’ to indicate that a network operation is in progress.  The
indicator disappears when all pending requests complete.


File: gdocs.info,  Node: Format conversion,  Next: Sync engine,  Prev: API client,  Up: Top

7 Format conversion
*******************

